'''''Star Wars Insider'' 73''' is the seventy-third issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[January 13]], [[2004]]. The subscriber-exclusive edition of issue 73 included the sixth volume of ''[[Bantha Tracks (department)|Bantha Tracks]]'', the [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Official ''Star Wars'' Fan Club]] newsletter.

==Contents==
===Departments===
*From the Editor's Desk
*[[Rebel Rumblings]]
*[[Star News]] {{C|by [[David Fein]] & ''Insider'' Staff}}
*[[Star Sightings]] {{C|by [[Benjamin Harper]]}}
*[[Best of Hyperspace]] {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*[[HoloNet News (Insider)|HoloNet News]] {{C|by Pablo Hidalgo}}
**[[Republic HoloNet News Core Edition 15:01:13]]
**[[CIS Shadowfeed Dispatch 15:01:15 Edition]]
*[[Gamescape]]
*[[Set Piece]] &mdash; Yavin 4 Rebel Base: Main Hangar {{C|by [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]]}}
*[[Bookshelf]] &mdash; The Fastest Pen in the Galaxy? {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*[[Comics Link]] &mdash; Battlefields {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*[[Scouting the Galaxy]] {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*[[Toy Box]] &mdash; Mindful of the Future {{C|by [[Hasbro]]}}
*[[Crossword (department)|Crossword]] &mdash; Keeping Score {{C|by [[Michael Selinker]]}}
*[[Star Wars Q&A|''Star Wars'' Q&A]] {{C|by Pablo Hidalgo}}
*[[The Last Page]] {{C|by [[Tony Moseley]]}}

===Features===
*"[[Prequel Update]]" {{C|by [[Jane Irene Kelly]]}}
*:<small>The latest on [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|Episode III]] from Producer [[Rick McCallum]].</small>
*"[[Return of the Jedi: Mark Hamill Comes Back to Broadway, the Big Screen and Prime Time]]" {{C|by [[Dave Gross]] & [[Jenny Scott]]}}
*:<small>An [[Star Wars Insider|''Insider'']] exclusive interview with the man who was [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]]: [[Mark Hamill]] takes the stage as a dance instructor in ''Six Dance Lessons in Six Weeks'', gets behind the camera with ''Comic Vook: The Movie'', and lends his voice to an animated TV host in ''The Wrong Coast''.</small>
*"[[A State of Nelvana: Droids & Ewoks Adventure Hour Revisited|A State of Nelvana: ''Droids & Ewoks Adventure Hour'' Revisited]]" {{C|by [[Shane Turgeon]]}}
*:<small>[[Cartoon Network]] wasn't the first studio to bring ''[[Star Wars]]'' characters to animated life. Travel back in time with the founders of [[Nelvana]] Studios, creators of the [[Star Wars: Droids: The Adventures of R2-D2 and C-3PO|''Droids'']] and [[Ewoks (television series)|''Ewoks'']] animated series.</small>
*"[[Dueling Jedi: Taking on Darth Maul in Episode I]]" {{C|by [[Ron Magid]]}}
*:<small>The first time [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] double teamed a [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]], his partner lost more than a hand. Go behind the scenes of one of the most thrilling [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] battles ever filmed.</small>
*"[[Radio Days: Revisiting the Star Wars Radio Dramas|Radio Days: Revisiting the ''Star Wars'' Radio Dramas]]" {{C|by [[Rich Handley]]}}
*:<small>If you haven't heard the [[Star Wars (radio)|NPR ''Star Wars'' radio dramas]], then you don't know the whole story of the [[original trilogy]]. The voice actors look back on their incarnations of the classic characters.</small>
*"[[The League of Spies]]" {{C|by [[Aaron Allston]]}}
*:<small>[[Joram Kithe]] and the [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone trooper]] known as [[Mapper]] trade the front lines for espionage duty, only to learn just how much of an oxymoron "military intelligence" can be.</small>

